	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was hoping some of you more experienced bards could make some recommendations for eqipment improvement for my lv 18 bard.  Right now she looks like a misfit with a mixture of chain, lambent, bronze, and leather looking equipment.  I'm not mega rich but I could probably put a couple hundred plat into upgrading a thing or two:<br><br>Head: Lumberjack Hat<br>Face: Turquoise Eyepatch<br>Earrings:  One +5ch One +3agi <br>Chest:  Brigandine Tunicc<br>Legs: Drakescale Leggings (+chr)<br>Waist: Drakescale Belt (+chr)<br>Boots:: Bronze<br>Wrists: One lambent bracer<br>Most everything else is banded<br>Weapons:  Barbed whip and some sort of claw I can't remember does around 6/26 or something like that.  Neither have a proc but both are magic.<br><br>Stength: 101<br>Dexterity: 101<br>Charisma: 98 <br><br>Wood Elf Bard<br><br>So as you can see, it doesn't look good.<br><br>Thanks for your help.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gabriarra Mistmoon<br>(31 Cleric High Elf)<br>Shaladarra Sowstorm<br>(30 druid wood elf)<br></td></tr>
