<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101046627882830></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101046627882830><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101046627882830>UBER</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101046627882830#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48595><span id= >yoconnor</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 8th 12:04 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just want everyone to know that after playing a paladin, necro, druid and bard... Bards are by far the most fun class in the game!  Since playing my bard to lvl 49 I've had no desire to play any of my other chars.  In fact I've stripped all my other chars and made my 49 bard a solo machine.  All SS minus bp(legs too). Fungi tunic. resist rings (+8).  Imbued granite spaulders. Siblisian berserker cloak. Axgoraths belt of defense. ice forged shackles. cougar claw earrings.  BoH, longsword of ethereal energy(primary/secondary) with di'zok wristsnapper in range.  Looking to twink a bard...do what I did and you'll have no problem charm kiting 2, then fear kiting the remaining mob for exp from 2 blue mobs at once and not even losing more than a bub of health...constant pull 2 mobs at a time and let the exp roll in... oh and as for instruments...selos drums of the march, lute of the howler, mcvaxius horn of war...and my crappy Brahhm's horn :(  Well worth the stripped main char and others as I can't get enough of the bard's amazing abilities and ability to get a group anywhere...and who cares if you can't... just solo.<br>Thraxus<br>Avenging Souls<br>49(oh so close to 50) Bard<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
